Building the model¶

In [23]:
def entropy(attribute):
    classes,tally = np.unique(attribute,return_counts = True)
    pi=[tally[i]/np.sum(tally) for i in range(len(classes))]
    entropy_value =-1* np.sum([pi*np.log2(pi)])
    return entropy_value
In [24]:
def info_gain(dataset,feature,label):
    dataset_entropy = entropy(dataset[label])   
    values,feat_counts= np.unique(dataset[feature],return_counts=True)
    weighted_feature_entropy = np.sum([(feat_counts[i]/np.sum(feat_counts))*entropy(dataset.where(dataset[feature]
                              ==values[i]).dropna()[label]) for i in range(len(values))])    
    return dataset_entropy - weighted_feature_entropy
In [25]:
def DecisionTree(dataset,label,parent=None):
    attributes=dataset.columns[:-1]
    datum= np.unique(dataset[label],return_counts=True)
    unique_data = np.unique(dataset[label])
    print("Entropy at root node:",entropy(dataset[label]))
    parent = unique_data[np.argmax(np.unique(dataset[label],return_counts=True)[1])]
    gains = [info_gain(dataset,i,label) for i in attributes]
    
    for i in range(len(attributes)):
        print("Column name:"+attributes[i]," Information gain: ",gains[i])
    return parent
